<TEXT>
<P>
 Comfort and Joy (A&E Tuesday at 1 a.m.), an amiable 1984 Bill Forsyth Scottish 
comedy, stars Bill Paterson as a deejay already going through some difficult 
changes when he becomes ensnared by an underworld conflict involving ice cream 
vans. 
</P>
<P>
 The Letter (Cinemax Thursday at noon) is the handsome 1940 William Wyler 
version of the Somerset Maugham drama. Set in Malaysia, the film stars Bette 
Davis as a colonial housewife with a terrible secret. 
