<P>
 ONE STEP CLOSER TO HOME by John McPherson (Andrews & McMeel: $6.95; 128 pp., 
paperback original). John McPherson's comic strip "Closer to Home" recalls Jim 
Unger's "Herman": a single panel depicting the daily disasters of frowzy women, 
lumpish men and their dumpy children. A small boy goes through his dad's ties 
while his older sister watches, holding Father's Day wrapping and yelling, "For 
cryin' out loud, just pick one! He's never going to recognize it!" McPherson's 
limited draftsmanship sometimes prevents his drawings from communicating as 
clearly as they should, but he's often very funny, and the development of his 
personal style will be entertaining to watch.  
