<HEADLINE>
<P>
LENDERS WEEPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My wife and I have gone through the travail of trying to get friends and 
family to return our books (so many times) that I decided to write a bookplate 
inscription. Here it is: 
</P>
<P>
 Would that I could keep them both:  
</P>
<P>
 The friend I love for all his faults,  
</P>
<P>
 The friend I call a favorite book.  
</P>
<P>
 Either I lend my friend my book,  
</P>
<P>
 And wait and wait and finally  
</P>
<P>
 Resign myself to the bereavement of its loss;  
</P>
<P>
 Or else I make a point to get it back,  
</P>
<P>
 And in the process of exposing his or her neglect  
</P>
<P>
 Alienate, to some extent, my friend.  
</P>
<P>
 JERRY COWLE, PACIFIC PALISADES 
</P>
