<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAME OF THE WEEK; WILSON SCORES QUICKLY, OFTEN IN 55-14 WIN; FOOTBALL: EAGLE 
ROCK'S DEFENSE IS NO MATCH FOR MULES QUARTERBACK EDDIE GONZALEZ, WHO PASSES FOR 
258 YARDS AND TWO TOUCHDOWNS AND RUSHES FOR TWO MORE SCORES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's the game that East Los Angeles has been waiting for. 
</P>
<P>
 Not the annual Garfield-Roosevelt grudge match, but next week's showdown 
between Franklin and Wilson that will likely determine the Northern Conference 
champion. 
</P>
<P>
 Franklin fired the first shot with a 41-7 drubbing of Verdugo Hills Friday 
afternoon and the Mules retaliated with a 55-14 dismantling of Eagle Rock 
Friday night at Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 The message is clear: Neither team is going to give an inch. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought this game would be the acid test even though I am surprised at the 
score," Wilson coach Eddie Martinez said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mules opened the game with an impressive seven-play, 3:12 drive that ended 
in a 10-yard touchdown pass from Eddie Gonzalez to Buster Bradley, giving 
Wilson a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson never looked back, scoring 27 of the game's next 34 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez, who threw for 258 yards and two touchdowns, accounted for four of 
Wilson's eight touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez scored twice in the second quarter on two-yard runs, the last of 
which boosted Wilson's lead to 28-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Arlin Slayton had 10 carries for 44 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Eagle Rock's Trenell Young had 86 yards in 22 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Records: Eagle Rock 4-2; Wilson 5-1 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Franklin at Wilson. 
</P>
