<P>
FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'WUTHERING HEIGHTS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This 1939 William Wyler version of Emily Bronte's passionate and inspired 
novel of l'amour on the lightning-lashed moors and gloomy heaths is the best 
and most successful on screen.With Laurence Olivier as Heathcliff and Merle 
Oberon as Cathy (both pictured), the film also features David Niven, Flora 
Robson, Donald Crisp and Geraldine Fitzgerald. The script is by Ben Hecht and 
Charles McArthur (AMC Wednesday at 10 a.m.). 
</P>
