<TEXT>
<P>
 Prince's long-unreleased, much-bootlegged "Black Album" may finally be coming 
out officially. Warner Bros. Records has tentative plans to release it next 
month.A finished new album, "The Gold Experience," has apparently been pushed 
back to next year amid uncertainty as to whether it will be issued by Warners 
or by NPG, the company that has handled releases by the mystery man under his " 
" identity. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the former Prince joined Nona Gaye in a new anti-gun public service 
TV spot. Gaye's father, singer Marvin Gaye, died after being shot by his own 
father 10 years ago. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Megadeth fans might want to track down copies of the band's new bio 
accompanying press mailings for the new "Youthanasia" album -- it was written 
by macabre author Dean Koontz, with tongue firmly in cheek. In one passage he 
notes that metal band bios are required to use words like thrashmasters , 
grizzly-throated and raging maniac , after which he simply writes, "Okay, 
there, I've used them." . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Beck is set to start recording his second Geffen album, which could be out by 
mid-'95. . . . Also about to start a new album is White Zombie. 
