<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITIC'S PICK: 'THE VANISHING' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kenneth Turan 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Psychological thrillers are only as effective as their villains, and this 1993 
film has a magnificent one.Barney Cousins is his name and, as played by Jeff 
Bridges (pictured), he is an only-too-believable maniac. Bridges' Barney is a 
college chemistry professor in the Pacific Northwest, a loving father and 
faithful husband, a man you could pass on the street without feeling mortal 
danger. Directed by George Sluizer, who also directed the original 1988 Dutch 
version. With Nancy Travis and Kiefer Sutherland (HBO Monday at 4:15 a.m.). 
Kenneth Turan 
</P>
</TEXT>
