<HEADLINE>
<P>
SKINHEAD ATTACK FAKED, GERMAN PROSECUTORS SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 German prosecutors said Friday that a woman who said she had been thrown out 
of a streetcar by skinheads after trying to protect an elderly woman had lied. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, whose tale stunned Germany and prompted police to put up a $13,000 
reward for help in finding the skinheads, lied about the attack because she 
wanted free medical treatment, the prosecutor's office in Potsdam said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
