<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OXNARD; WORKSHOP OFFERED ON RAISING FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard financial firm will hold a workshop Tuesday on a popular 
fund-raising method for Ventura County nonprofit organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 IDS Financial Services will host a presentation by Russ Charvonia, one of its 
financial consultants, on "Planned Giving," a way for nonprofit organizations 
to receive large gifts while donors get a tax deduction and an income for life. 
Most nonprofit organizations raise money through planned giving programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The free workshop will take place from noon to 1:30 p.m. at the IDS offices on 
the 14th floor of the Union Bank Building, 300 E. Esplanade Drive. Lunch will 
also be provided. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations and information call 981-4120. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
