<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OXNARD; 5 HELD ON SUSPICION OF SELLING, USING HEROIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five Oxnard residents were arrested on suspicion of selling and using heroin 
at a local motel, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrests marked the end of a six-week investigation that began when 
neighbors of the E-Z Motel in the 500 block of East Date Street in Oxnard 
complained about blatant narcotic dealing in motel rooms and the parking lot, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested on suspicion of being under the influence were Alma Rosa Martinez, 
33; Tamara Christine Ervin, 22, and Mona Lisa Mejia, 22, police said. Charles 
Smith, 22, and Jorge Blanco Mendez, 20, were arrested on suspicion of selling 
heroin, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez, Ervin and Mejia have been released from Ventura County Jail. Smith 
and Mendez were being held Saturday in lieu of $20,000 bail, authorities said. 
CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
