<P>
HOME BIRTH EXPERIENCE NOT WITHOUT DANGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was extremely angered by the selfishness of Joanne and Bruce Shannahoff in 
relating their home birth experience ("Couple Finds Birth at Home Empowering, 
Safe and Comfortable," Oct. 4). 
</P>
<P>
 Although this couple was seemingly well-educated and well-prepared, their 
comments in regard to this "empowering" choice reeked of the me-generation. 
</P>
<P>
 Granted, birth is a natural event, but complications do arise and not 
infrequently. Immediate intervention by an obstetrician in a delivery room 
could mean the difference between life and death. 
</P>
<P>
 No place in the article was this most important issue addressed. 
