<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEHERE IS ON A ROLL IN CLIPPER VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terry Dehere scored 18 of his game-high 27 points in the second quarter as the 
Clippers defeated the Atlanta Hawks, 106-84, in an exhibition Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hawks, who played without holdout center-forward Kevin Willis and injured 
center Jon Koncak, emptied their bench in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Two dunks by Charles Outlaw and a three-pointer by Dehere gave the Clippers a 
52-45 lead they did not relinquish. 
</P>
<P>
 Harold Ellis added 19 points, Outlaw 14 and Loy Vaught 10 points and 12 
rebounds for the Clippers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
