PARADISE CREEK EASY WINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paradise Creek scored a 5 1/2-length victory in the Grade I Washington 
International at Laurel Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Paradise Creek ran the 1 1/4 miles on the turf in 1:59 and paid $2.40, $2.20 
and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
 California-based Soviet Problem won the $200,000 Laurel Dash by 1 1/4 lengths, 
running six furlongs on turf in a stakes-record 1:09. 
