<P>
OVERLOOKING RAPE OF UNITED AIRLINES FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After reading your article on the United Airlines Shuttle start-up ("Shuttle 
Launch," Sept. 29), it would appear that one of the big problems with the 
airline is completely overlooked. 
</P>
<P>
 I refer to the very large multimillion-dollar buyout of its former CEO, 
Stephen Wolf. And as I read in the Wall Street Journal, one of their top 
executives was forced out of his position in a European company. I wonder how 
long it will be before UAL buys out its present top executives. How long will 
this rape of UAL funds go on? 
</P>
<P>
 GEORGE DOTTL 
</P>
