NON-KUDOS TO DRIVERS OF MTA'S BUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I'm writing in response to Jeannette K. Multer of Los Angeles, who commends 
the Metropolitan Transit Authority drivers ("Kudos to the Drivers of MTA's 
Buses," Letters, Oct. 2). 
</P>
<P>
 I am 14 and don't have a driver's license, so I depend on the buses.Many times 
when I've had to take the MTA to school, I'm standing at the bus stop waving my 
money in the air, thinking the bus will pick me up. To my surprise, the bus 
goes right past me. The next bus doesn't come for another hour. 
</P>
