<HEADLINE>
<P>
'LIGHTS, CAMERA, ORCHIDS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOEL RAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The magnificent cymbidium orchid pictured on the front page is just one of 
thousands of beautiful orchids that will be on display next weekend, Oct. 
21-23, at the Eighth Annual East West Orchid Show, to be held at the New Otani 
Hotel and Garden, 120 S. Los Angeles St. 
</P>
<P>
 This year's show is themed "Lights, Camera, Orchids" and will feature 39 
glamorous displays using thousands of exotic blooms grown by members of local 
orchid societies and growers as far away as Thailand and Japan.Show hours are 
10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Friday and Saturday, and 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. next Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Some displays will salute legendary Hollywood movies such as "The African 
Queen," and others will utilize movie cameras, posters and other Hollywood 
accouterment to carry out the show-biz theme. Besides the displays themselves, 
there will be continuous activities, lectures and seminars including tips on 
repotting, dividing, corsage design and flower arrangement. The show and all 
events are free and open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 You will also be able to purchase orchid plants for very reasonable prices 
from 23 commercial growers and nurseries in the Hotel's adjacent Weller Court 
Shopping Center. 
</P>
