<TEXT>
<P>
 In today's Times, Traveling in Style magazine follows in the footsteps of the 
famous -- to Charles Darwin's Galapagos Islands, Thomas Jefferson's Paris, 
Edward Hopper's New York and Ernest Hemingway's many haunts. We also linger 
where the renowned lived -- in Jamaica, once the home of neighbors Noel Coward 
and Ian Fleming, and Capri, at one time a favorite refuge of Roman Emperor 
Tiberius. 
</P>
