<HEADLINE>
<P>
COSTLY CRUISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I enjoy the travel articles by Shawn Hubler, especially her "All Aboard!" 
(Sept. 18), but I sometimes wonder if Ms. Hubler knows how the other half 
lives. 
</P>
<P>
 A family of four that can afford $7,200 for a Caribbean cruise, even if it is 
all inclusive, is hardly the norm in this area. In some families, $7,200 is the 
entire annual income. In these times of companies downsizing, mass layoffs and 
very few comparable jobs to replace those lost, $7,200 cruises are about as 
attainable for many people as a trip to the moon. 
</P>
<P>
 JUNE MOFFETT 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 
</P>
