<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARK FUHRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re O.J. Simpson case: My sister was murdered last year. Her case, in the midst 
of so many other unresolved homicides in Los Angeles, was shuffled between 
various detectives with limited time and experience to offer.It wasn't until my 
sister's case was given to Detective Mark Fuhrman that I saw any real progress 
or interest taken. 
</P>
<P>
 Not only did he express sincere empathy toward me and my family over the loss, 
but he's put forth the groundwork and effort needed to conduct a more solid 
investigation. My calls never go unreturned and as a Latin American who is 
sensitive to prejudice, I never once detected that Fuhrman manifested an 
offensive attitude or comments. 
</P>
<P>
 I wonder how many citizens actually understand the mental pressures of working 
in crime-infested areas and the tragedies witnessed. I can only imagine that 
the ability to maintain a balanced vision would be continually challenging. 
</P>
<P>
 BESSY NORIEGA 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
