<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH LOS ANGELES; REDEVELOPMENT PLAN TO BE WEIGHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 South-Central residents are encouraged to attend a Community Redevelopment 
Agency meeting at 6 p.m. Oct. 25 at New Hope Baptist Church, 5200 S. Central 
Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The Council District 9 Community Advisory Committee meeting will consider 
approval of a preliminary plan to establish a redevelopment project in a 
5,600-acre area.The project area is bounded by the Santa Monica Freeway on the 
north, 84th Street on the south, Alameda and Central avenues on the east and 
roughly Vermont Avenue on the west. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee recommended creation of the redevelopment project to help 
rebuild the parts of Council District 9 that were damaged during the spring 
1992 riots and January's Northridge quake. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Rita Walters is scheduled to attend the meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-1707. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
