<HEADLINE>
<P>
3RD SUSPECT SOUGHT IN FATAL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police continued to search for a third suspect in the weekend shooting death 
of a local 19-year-old man who was attacked after he "exchanged looks" with his 
killers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two others who allegedly participated in the Friday-night shooting -- 
20-year-old Anne Marie Barajas of North Hollywood and a 15-year-old girl from 
Sun Valley -- were booked on suspicion of murder shortly after the incident, 
said Detective Mike Langston of the San Fernando Police Department.The girl's 
name was not released because of her age. 
</P>
<P>
 Langston said Javier Rodriguez of San Fernando was in a mini-mall in the 1000 
block of North Maclay Street about 9:15 p.m. Friday when he was approached by 
two women and a man in a car. Witnesses told police Rodriguez was shot 
following a verbal exchange with the people in the car. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Barajas and the 15-year-old, who are not related, after 
locating the vehicle believed to have been used in the incident, Langston said. 
</P>
<P>
 Langston said the two did not appear to know Rodriguez, but that "there was an 
exchange of looks between the suspect and the victim." 
</P>
