<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: AUSTIN NAMED SERVICES DIVISION PRESIDENT AT UNIHEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dr. John H. Austin has been named president of the professional services 
division of Burbank-based Unihealth. In the newly created position, Austin will 
oversee the activities of the medical group MSOs, medical foundations and 
medical groups affiliated with the nonprofit Unihealth network. 
</P>
<P>
 For the past two years, Austin has operated his own Northern California-based 
managed-care consulting firm. 
</P>
<P>
 Before that he was executive vice president of Health Plan of America, 
responsible for all aspects of its health care delivery system. 
</P>
<P>
 * Keith M. Beckwith has been appointed vice president of sales for Digital 
Sound Corp., a Carpinteria, Calif.-based supplier of high-capacity 
network-based message-processing systems. Beckwith, who has been with Digital 
Sound for eight years, will be responsible for worldwide sales efforts. 
Previously, he was a senior field sales executive at Intel Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard C. Callister and Jennifer C. Sanders have joined Compensation Resource 
Group Inc. as senior vice presidents in the firm's Pasadena headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Callister, who was previously with the Los Angeles law firm of Sheppard, 
Mullin, Richter & Hampton, has also been named general counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 Before joining CRG, Sanders was associated with Management Compensation Group 
in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Compensation Resource Group Inc. is a national firm specializing in the design 
and implementation of executive compensation and benefit plans.  
</P>
<P>
 The investment banking and securities brokerage firm of Hambrecht & Quist Inc. 
announced the appointment of Daniel H. Case III as president and chief 
executive. William R. Hambrecht, founder of the firm, will continue as chairman 
and remain active in the firm. Case, has been with the San Francisco 
headquarters since 1979. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven T. Honda has been promoted to senior vice president and chief financial 
officer of Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco. Kenneth C. Miller has been 
named vice president of financial risk management. Before joining the bank in 
1993, Honda held various positions at Bank of America, Security Pacific and 
First Interstate Bank of California.  
</P>
<P>
 Miller, formerly senior vice president and asset-liability manager at First 
Nationwide Bank, will oversee the bank's $5-million mortgage-backed securities 
investment portfolio.  
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Jordan has been named vice president of development and planning for 
Disney Store, Worldwide in Glendale. Previously, he was vice president of 
strategic planning for the firm's parent company, Burbank-based Walt Disney Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
