<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PRICE OF PUNISHMENT; A PRISON EXPLOSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the past decade, California has built and opened 16 prisons and several 
minimum security camps, and made major renovations and additions to the 12 
prisons which existed when the state embarked on the nation's most expensive 
prison construction program. Four other prisons are being built and 
construction is scheduled to begin shortly on two others. Here is a look at the 
expansion of the state prison system. Opened Since 1984 
</P>
<P>
 1. Solano 
</P>
