<HEADLINE>
<P>
8 TONS OF COCAINE SEIZED; EX-SUMO WRESTLER CLAIMS HUNGER MADE HIM A PURSE 
SNATCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A retired sumo wrestler, known for his insatiable appetite, was arrested for 
grabbing a handbag from an elderly woman in downtown Tokyo because he needed 
money for food, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tomohisa Fujino, 22, was arrested after he snatched a handbag containing 6,000 
yen ($60) from the 73-year-old woman. 
</P>
<P>
 Fujino, fighting under the ring name Hoshiryuma, climbed to the third-highest 
division in the sport but retired in 1990 because of back injury. 
</P>
<P>
 "I eat twice as much as the average person, and I couldn't keep it up," police 
quoted him as saying. 
</P>
<P>
 Fujino, who weighs more than 220 pounds, had been trying to make ends meet by 
doing odd jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
