<HEADLINE>
<P>
8 TONS OF COCAINE SEIZED; PASSENGER TRAINS COLLIDE IN ENGLAND, KILLING 5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two passenger trains collided in dense morning fog near this south England 
village Saturday, killing five people and injuring 11, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both train drivers were among the dead, said Rail Track, the company which 
operates the single-track line. 
</P>
<P>
 The trains, each with six cars and carrying only 19 passengers between them, 
should have passed each other on a loop further up the rail track. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowden is about 24 miles south of central London. 
</P>
