<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; LONG BEACH STATE GAINS 17-16 WATER POLO VICTORY OVER UC SAN 
DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tim Ault, Ian Taylor and Greg Finley scored goals in double overtime to lift 
Long Beach State to a 17-16 victory over UC San Diego in a nonconference water 
polo game Saturday at Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach led, 7-4, at halftime, but San Diego scored five goals in each of 
the final two quarters.The Tritons' Craig Gruber scored a two-point goal to 
send the game into overtime.  
</P>
<P>
 Ault led Long Beach (4-13) with six goals and Joaquin Felsmann added four. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State 3, San Jose State 1 -- Brita Schwerm had 21 kills to lead 
10th-ranked Long Beach State (13-3, 8-1), 15-10, 3-15, 15-7, 15-7. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, Concordia 1 -- Genevie Wright had 18 kills and 
Angela Tonavanik had three consecutive solo blocks to lead Southern California 
College (16-6, 5-4). Concordia fell to 11-11, 2-7. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Colorado College volleyball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman finishes second -- Shawna Parkinson had 19 kills as Chapman (18-5) 
defeated host Colorado College in three games, 15-7, 15-8, 15-10, to finish 
second in the tournament at Colorado Springs, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 In Mountain Pacific Sports Federation water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific 8, UC Irvine 7 -- Rey Rivera, Axel Wohlfarth and Matt Radke scored two 
goals each for Pacific (13-5). Peter Muller had two goals and a two-point goal 
for host UCI (5-10). 
</P>
<P>
 In the New Mexico State Golf Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine third -- Jesse Lanham shot a one-over par 73, finishing sixth, to lead 
the Anteaters to a third-place tie with San Diego State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
