<P>
SENIORS AT RISK TOO IN 6TH STREET AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the articles about the (Santa Ana) police sweep on 3rd Street, one fact has 
been overlooked: There is within the 6th Street territory a senior apartment 
complex just south of Flower Park. About two blocks away, at 1st and Ross 
streets, there are two more senior complexes.All of these complexes have had 
break-ins and, within the last two weeks, the complexes on Ross have each had a 
violent break-in that resulted in the resident being sent to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 In all the years I have lived here, I have always made it a point to not get 
off the bus, even just across the street, after dark, which means I must be 
home by 5 p.m. in the winter. How about remembering the seniors who are in 
danger as well as showing concern for the families who live in the area? 
</P>
<P>
 JUANITA MATASSA, Santa Ana 
