<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE SEEKING COUPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are seeking a man who smashed a window in his girlfriend's home and 
possibly abducted her. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove Police Sgt. Scott Watson said Cynthia Jane Melson, 24, has called 
family members three times to tell them she is OK, but that police are 
continuing to investigate it as a possible kidnaping after receiving reports 
that her boyfriend, identified as Joseph Ray McBath, dragged her to his car. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have not located her to confirm" that she is safe, Watson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
